history.content: For 162, students will actually re-shuffle discussion section assignments based largely on project groups in consultation with the instructor and TAs after the class begins so the section you are initially signed up for is only of minimal importance. You will need to be able to attend the discussion section your project group gets assigned to (based in part on your collective availability).

I am enrolled in a thursday 2pm section, but my schedule has changed and I have a conflict. I have heard that using the "Options" section of CalCentral may put me back on the waitlist, so I don't want to risk it. Can I go to a different section after classes start? Or is there any way for me to switch sections safely?

Thanks!
history.subject: CS 162: attend different section from the one I am enrolled in?
